review_blob: Tried this at the 2007 Arborfest, it was served on Cask.  Great hop aroma, clean start and finish, great pale ale, with a heavy hop twist.

Clean aroma (this threw be off the first few beers, you say Hop, I expect smell).   OH CRAP, i tried SO hard to get an aroma, i sniffed this beer up my nose.  Honestly, I can smell it now, but i think it hs to do with the fact that i sniffed the beer up my nose.  Anyway, I didnt like this beer at first.  I was to stuck on it being an IPA.  It aint an IPA.   Light start and finish.  Definitely a has hops in it, kind of on the sweet side (down non hoppy beer drinkers).  Very light in color,  slightly hazy.  The only thing that might get in your way of liking/loveing this beer, is getting stuck on what you think it should be.  It is what it is, and it is good. Wallop!

Crack!  The minute the can is open you can smell this S.O.B., and that is a good thing  Go ahead, sniff right out of the can, that aint no Coors Light.  Ummmm, smells good.  Lets get a glass, hopefully a a glass that is Surly Swag of course.  Gluub, glub, glub, ahhh aint she pretty.  Amber in color with a bit of haze.  Your first gulp you can still smell this beer like crazy.  Clean start, bite (big bite) of hops, and a clean finish.  Where is my next can?

As of this writing this is the only Norwegian beer I ever had.  This beer tells me they are on to something.  Cloudy appearance, light amber in color.  But then WHAM, the flavor of light malt and hops hits your nose, then your tounge, then your throat.  Ahhhh.
Golden colored with light head.  Taste is fresh and crisp, with a sweet after taste.

The magic is that the beer does not taste "flavored" by the chipotle pepper, but infused into its character.  At first you taste a beer that reminds you of smoke and heat, but as your pallete warms up to the unique beer you start to distinctly taste and smell the chipotle pepper.  I was very happy with the Chipotle Ale.

This made me think of what a Heiniken could be, instead of skunky grass.  Makes me think that I might actually like heiniken after tasting Carlsberg Beer.  I will be adding this to the rotation of easy to drink beers kept on hand.

This is the top of the beer food chain for my liking.  Did not score it perfect because it would mean that I no longer need to search for the perfect beer.  
Overall great color, flavor, aroma, and aftertaste.  Plus, a bottle of this at 10% will start or end your night with a little WOW.
Being a NE Minneapolis resident I have a warm spot for a cold "Primo".   Light as a Miller Light in color, taste is a traditional lager with a hint of sweet.
